===Noun===
'''minion'''

#<!--DefA-->A loyal servant of another, usually more powerful being.
#<!--DefB--> (''Biblical tradition'')  in Christian [[angelology]], the sixth level of [[angel]]s, ranked above [[principality|principalities]] and below [[throne]]s
#<!--DefC-->Term used in the farming industry to describe the amount of one million [[onion]]s.
#<!--DefD-->In [[Fantasy Literature]], animals turned to the service of evil. Common minions include: shape-shifting sneaky [[cyborg]] leopards, throat-ripping [[yorkshire terriers]] armed with machine guns, minature mind-controlled sneaky mechanical badgers, insane robot sharks, mind-controlled [[vampire]] hippos, telepathic yorkshire terriers that are immune to bullets, sneaky genetically-engineered [[lemming]]s, invisible sneaky [[capybaras]] with self-destruct devices, etc...


